            <div class="narrative"><p>Yes, the line is volatile — Bitcoin is volatile. But look at the <em>direction</em>. In 2013, you needed 367 bitcoin to buy the median US house. By 2025, you needed roughly 5. That's a 98.6% decline in the bitcoin-denominated cost of housing. <strong>No amount of fiat appreciation in home values can disguise what is happening on this chart.</strong> The house is demonetizing — shedding its store-of-value premium — as bitcoin absorbs the monetary energy that was artificially trapped in real estate. The trend line tells you where this is heading, even if the path is jagged.</p></div>

